The ostensible object of CHREMES'S journey to Lemnos was to collect the rents of some estates owned there by his rich wife NAUSISTRATA3 his real purpose to bring back with him to Athens a young girl, ΡΗΛΝΙυΜ, his daughter by a second wife whom he has secretly married, under the name of STILPO‚ in one of his previous visits to that island.
